description:
YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

The primary responsibilities of this role, Senior Biotech Data Scientist, are to:
• Work with partners across the Biotech organization to turn data into critical information and knowledge for improved process understanding to facilitate data driven decisions making;
• Query large sets of structured and unstructured data from disparate sources, clean and validate the data to ensure accuracy, completeness, and uniformity for analysis;
• Perform advanced statistical analyses and data mining using state of the art methods, develop mathematical models to simulate biomanufacturing processes or cellular functions and behavior;
• Develop stories and visualizations to effectively communicate complex analysis’ in clear, precise and actionable manner and work with data engineering teams to industrialize respective data science products;
• Provide technical assessments based on statistics, data analysis and process knowledge, document findings and communicate to... help partners understand and interpret results and recommendations;
• Lead cross-functional teams and train junior data scientists;
• Use own and leverage others business domain knowledge to design and scope studies and data analytics approaches and to determine appropriate statistics, algorithms, machine learning models, data sets and variables.

This role is open to applicants that require domestic relocation
